 Campaign newsletter July 08
	Forward to your friends
Dear Jean-Philippe,

With only weeks to go until the start of the Olympic Games,=20
Amnesty International has delivered China's President Hu Jintao a=20
list of five actions that will go some way to living up to the=20
country's human rights obligations.

Published as an open letter from Secretary General Irene Khan, the=20
list includes releasing all prisoners of conscience, publishing=20
full statistics on the death penalty and allowing full and=20
unrestricted media freedom for Chinese and international=20
journalists in the lead-up to the Games and beyond.

Irene Khan says while China has made efforts to address some=20
longstanding human rights concerns, these developments=20
notwithstanding, the preparation for the Olympics has actually had=20
a negative impact in some areas of human rights.

Read the letter in full
http://uncensor.com.au/uncensor/blog/amnestys_to_do_list_for_chinas_hu_ji=
ntao/?utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_content=3D09Jul2008
=20
In this edition

    * Call on Microsoft to allow online freedom
    * Support victims of torture
    * Support a National Plan of Action
