    * Work at Amnesty International

Support victims of torture

Following on from the International day of support for victims of=20
torture on 26 June, we're continuing to demand the release of=20
Abdusalam al-Hela, who has been subjected to secret detention,=20
torture and denial of medical care since 2002. After being arrested=20
in Egypt and held illegally and in secret in Afghanistan for two=20
years he was moved to Guantanamo Bay in 2004, where he has been=20
subjected to torture and other cruel, inhuman and degrading=20
treatment.

Call on the US Government to release Abdusalam al-Hela
http://action.amnesty.org.au/centre/action/13983/?utm_source=3Dnewsletter=
&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_content=3D09Jul2008

Support a National Plan of Action

Amnesty International has released a report that could provide a=20
blueprint for an Australian National Plan of Action to eliminate=20
violence against women.

Drawing on the findings of the United Nations and other=20
international organisations as well as the experience of many=20
countries, the report calls for a good practice, human rights=20
approach to the National Plan. You can find out more about our=20
research and findings here.
http://action.amnesty.org.au/svaw/comments/14454/?utm_source=3Dnewsletter=
&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_content=3D09Jul2008

The Government is currently inviting submissions from organisations=20
and individuals on what should be included in a national plan. We=20
encourage you to take this unique opportunity to directly=20
contribute to policy to eliminate violence against women.

Find out details of the submission process
http://www.ofw.facsia.gov.au/womens_safety_agenda/national_council_reduce=
_violence.htm?utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_content=3D09=
Jul2008

Vision 2014: Activist consultation

We're in the process of setting our vision to 2014, looking at the=20
areas in which we can make the greatest human rights impact.

We invite all activists and supporters to get involved and have a=20
say in the future direction of the organisation. Have a look at=20
our proposed vision then let us know your views - we value your=20
contribution.
http://action.amnesty.org.au/page/vision2014?utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_=
medium=3Demail&utm_content=3D09Jun2008

Fill in our survey
http://action.amnesty.org.au/page/vision2014?utm_source=3Dnewsletter&utm_=
medium=3Demail&utm_content=3D09Jul2008

