t:0;" >Call on Microsoft to allow online freedom</h2>=20
<p>Microsoft is aiding the repression of freedom of expression and inform=
ation in China by complying with Chinese Government requests that result =
in censorship of the internet.</p>
<p>It filters the results of politically-sensitive searches and removes b=
logs critical of the Chinese Government. This censorship contradicts the =
very principles and values that Microsoft was founded upon.</p>
