left:0;" >Letters of thanks</h2>=20
<p>Amnesty International has received letters from two prisoners we have =
worked with to thank our members and activists for their support.</p>
<p>Recently-released Guant&#225;namo Bay detainee Sami al-Hajj wrote to t=
hank everyone who wrote letters to him. He received 10,000 letters while =
in detention and says he will never forget their help. <a href=3D"http://=
amnestyinternationalaustralia.cmail2.com/l/457503/86dc4jr/0" style=3D"col=
or:#000;" >Read his reply</a>.</p>
<p>Chinese human rights defender Zeng Jinyan, wife of recently jailed act=
ivist Hu Jia, also wrote to express her deep thanks and gratitude for all=
 the letters of support she has received since her husband&#8217;s impris=
onment, which help her realise she is not alone through her ongoing house=
 arrest.</p>
<p><a href=3D"http://amnestyinternationalaustralia.cmail2.com/l/457503/86=
dc4jr/c" style=3D"color:#000;" >Read Zeng Jinyan's letter</a></p>
